			<abstract label="Abstract:" encodinganalog="520$a">Consists of audio cassette tapes of
				interviews conducted by Joe Toyoshima in 1966 as an oral history of Sinclair. Also
				included are photocopies of articles relating to Liberty Hill, to the dockworkers'
				strike of 1923, and to the Industrial Workers of the World. One of the articles,
				accompanied by three color photographs, details the Liberty Hill Commemorative
				Marker dedicated as California State Historical Monument No. 1021, May 9, 1998, the
				75th anniversary of the dockworkers' strike at San Pedro/Los Angeles Harbor. A
				cassette of songs of the I.W.W. and of migrant workers, four of which are
				compositions by Joe Hill, completes the collection. </abstract>
		</did>
